Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_mutex_condition(25.10)                          set_mutex_condition(25.10)

Name
       set_mutex_condition

Syntax
       set_mutex_condition

       [-help]

       [<netNames>]

       Allows  the  software  to use one of the specified attackers - each at-
       tacker is then evaluated and the worst one (for each victim net) is se-
       lected.

       This command applies a mutex group to a set of attackers (for a victim)
       to reduce pessimism. A mutex group is a group of nets of which only one
       can transition in a given cycle.

       Parameters

       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       <netNames>
              Specifies the net names of the mutex group.

Examples
              * The following example shows that only  one  of  the  specified
                nets, between abc[0-3], can switch at any given point of time:

                set_mutex_condition {abc[0] abc[1] abc[2] abc[3]}

                Each  of  the  specified  attackers  will be evaluated and the
                worst one will be used.

Related Information
              * report_mutex_condition

